6:
Congratulations, you're our 314th
customer of the day!
7:
As luck would have it, you've won
yourself a grand prize!
9:
Come on in and have a gander at
your gift!
16:
Wh-whoa, what's the big idea,
Suizen?
21:
Ah, perhaps I overreacted just a tad.
My apologies.
24:
You say that I am today's 314th
customer, and yet I can practically
hear crickets chirping from how
empty your store is.
27:
Still, I'm not heartless enough to walk
away from someone in need. If you'll
be honest from now on, I'll listen to
what you have to say about your
troubles.
31:
You need a guy to be your promo
boy?
33:
Yeah... You see, our shopping district
decided to have all the stores
participate in one big White Fest
promo.
34:
But our business is already short on
hands, and our budget is tight
enough as is—
35:
So you decided to rope a customer
into helping.
38:
Normally I'd berate you for how
foolish such a plan would be, but for
someone who's been driven into a
corner, it's an impressive gamble.
43: I also think it was an interesting idea.
47:
Uh, Suizen. Don't tell me you're
wearing that outfit because you're
actually gonna help them...
53:
But of course. You know me, always
interfering with other people's
business. If I can help someone,
then I will do all I can to assist.
59:
Then let's get started immediately,
shall we? Firstly, there are many
issues with your store beyond just
the White Fest preparations...
61:
The most egregious of which is the
negative energy dwelling within the
place. You're going to attract more
than a few nasty customers if this
keeps up.
64: H-how do we go about fixing that?
66:
By changing the flow of thoughts
that occur in these walls.
Redecorating and adjusting your
business model should do the trick.
68:
To do that, I'll need you to go over
your business in detail and teach
me everything you've been doing—
71:
I'll do it! Whatever you need, I'll
provide!
79:
That smile is giving me seriously
bad vibes...
93:
Hey. What're you looking all
constipated for?
98:
Trying to think up a new sweet...
Suizen said he'd do it, but I figured I
should help somehow—
102:
You sure he even needs it? He looks
like he's already come up with
something.
107:
You've come at a good time. Would
you like to help with tasting my test
sample?
111:
Wait... Huh?! You already finished
making it...
116:
That's because I used an already
existing recipe. This is a popular
sweet from the East.
125:
My tongue... The flavors! The texture!
This is amazing!
129:
Bit too sweet for my tastes, but hey...
not bad. I think Stella and the others
would be super into it.
134:
Gosh, Suizen... You really can do
anything you put your mind to, huh?
138: Within reason. I know my limits.
141:
Anyway, if I have your seal of
approval, then this should do fine on
our new menu.
143:
All that's left is to unveil my trump
card. Might as well use everything
within my repertoire, now that I've
come this far.
149:
Welcome, ladies. 
We hope you'll enjoy your visit.
153: Stay as long as you like.
158:
This is crazy. I'm blown away.
Seriously...
162:
You should work your own charm
too, you know?
166: ...Why help out to this extent though?
169:
To facilitate the forming of bonds. 
I have a feeling this town will be a
place where many destinies
intertwine.
171:
Besides, I wanted to take this
chance to test out a new curse.
182:
I must say, it's interesting how
utilizing curses is similar to
conducting business.
186: Vigilance is key for success in either.
189:
Welcome. I'll be with you in just a
moment.
198:
But I guess if he's having fun, then
that's what counts.
